description.plain:
Stella Rose Bennett (born January 30, 2000), known professionally as BENEE (formerly Bene), is a New Zealand singer-songwriter who debuted in December 2017 with “Tough Guy.” Music had always been part of her life, with a family history in theatre. BENEE’s first instrument was a saxophone, playing it for several years, along with the guitar.

BENEE started posting music to Soundcloud in her final year of high school (2017), catching the attention of producer Josh Fountain. The pair went on the work together in several of her singles, including break-out single “Soaked” which was featured on triple j’s hottest 100 (2018).

After spending two weeks in a communications course at the Auckland Institute of Technology, Benee realised she wanted to be making music full-time.

BENEE’s debut EP, FIRE ON MARZZ was released in June 2019, and featured four previously released singles, alongside two new tracks. This was followed by a second EP, in November 2020, which included a feature from tourmate Jack Berry and American musician Gus Dapperton.

Her song “Supalonely” went viral on Tiktok in March 2020, becoming BENEE’s first song on the Billboard Hot 100, peaking at #39.

In May 2020, BENEE released a second version of the song, without Gus, titled “Lownely” and offering a more stripped back production. A month later, BENEE joined forces with Bakar and Kenny Beats to create “Night Garden”. The track was debuted on Apple Music in celebration of BENEE being named as their Up Next artist of the month. Further singles a the time included “Snail”, “Plain” and “Happen To Me”, eventually leading up to her debut album, Hey u x.

Through 2021, she released two collaborative singles, “help herself” with bbno$ and “ARE YOU LETTING GO?” with Dreamer Boy, as well as a solo single, “Doesn’t Matter.”

2022 brought another new solo single, “Beach Boy”, which was first teased on her official Discord server, 10 days before its release. This lead up to her third studio EP, Lychee. A number of collaborations proceeded after the EP, including tracks with Sub Urban, easy life and Jeremy Zucker.

During the early days of 2023, BENEE began teasing her first single of the year “Green Honda,” which she had been performing across the world during touring, as well as “Morning Routine.” Two brand new tracks were performed during her performance at Coachella 2023, “Sports Mode” and “Love Rollercoaster,” which appear on her album released later that year.

songs.title: Supalonely

description.plain:
“Supalonely” is the third single from the EP Stella & Steve. The song gained popularity in March 2020, after it went viral on TikTok.

The song was written during a trip to Los Angeles, following a break-up that inspired BENEE to write “Supalonely” and “Blu.”. She explained the song’s sound to i-D in February 2020:

Sometimes when you’re sad you’re just like, ugh, get over it! I think when I listen to music like “Supalonely” where it’s making fun of the feeling of being sad, in a way it kind of makes me feel good in a very weird way. When I hear “Supalonely” now and when I perform it I feel happy.

During Elton John’s Rocket Hour radio show on Apple Music in March 2020, he expressed his love for the song, inviting BENEE to join him on-air. In an Instagram post Elton said:

Supalonely by @beneemusic is my top tip for the next global smash. Love her and her music. #NewZealandRocks

songs.title: Glitter

description.plain:
“Glitter” is an alternative pop track, inspired by a night out early in BENEE’s career, where a bottle of glitter was dumped on her head. The song is one of her earliest hits, after going viral on TikTok in late 2019.

The track premiered on Australian radio station triple j just hours before her debut EP, FIRE ON MARZZ, that the track features on was released. To announce its radio premiere, BENEE posted a snippet of the chorus to her various social media accounts.

songs.title: Night Garden

description.plain:
On July 8, 2020, BENEE took to social media to share a video promoting an unreleased track, titled “Night Garden.” When reversed , the video plays a snippet of the song, which features a heavy bassline.

The song illuminates BENEE’s fear of being watched, a theme that has also been explored in her November 2019 track “Monsta” where BENEE sings about a monster watching her and eventually saving her.

“Night Garden” was debuted on Apple Music via Beats 1 with Zane Lowe. Earlier in the week BENEE has been revealed as Apple Music’s Up Next artist, the first person from New Zealand to receive the award.
